               <head>Guldastah-yi Bihar</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Guldastah-'i Bihār by Rāy Bihārī Rām</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85129379 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85076229 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85104368 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115920 http://lccn.loc.gov/n83158321" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4043-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7658">Rāy Bihārī Rām</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_f7658" type="supplied">راى بهارى رام</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21965">Guldastah-'i Bihār</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21965">گلدستهٴ بهار</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Excerpts from a larger collection of letters found in the library of Rajah Chhabelah Ram of Gujarat, the compilor's paternal uncle, put into order for educational purposes and as a memorial to his ancestors (aslāf)</p>
                        <p>Fragments consist of the beginning and very end portions, amounting to approximately a third of the orginal work</p>
                        <p>The author variously worked as munshīʾ for Sayyid ʿAbd Allāh Khān the mīr jumlah, Rawshan al-Dawlah Ẓafar Khān, and finally the vazīr al-mamālik, Chīn Qilīch Khān Āṣaf Jāh, under whose patronage he was appointed the nāʾib dīvān-i khāliṣah-yi sharīfah</p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>Transcribed by order of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7663" role="fmo">G. J. Nicholls</persName>, Judge at <name type="place">Farrukhabad</name>, from a manuscript obtained from <name type="place">Agra</name>
                     </note>
                     <filiation>Copied from a damaged and fragmentary manuscript completed at Shāhjahānābād, 9 Rabīʿ al-S̲ānī 1139 / 1726, in the reign of Emperor Muḥammad Shāh</filiation>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
